        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>When the hotpot is almost ready, reboil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>blanched peas</strong> to a pot, cover them with boiling water (just enough to cover them), bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 1 min or until they're warmed through</p><p>Once ready, drain and return to the pot, then stir through a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> with the <strong>chopped mint</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave out the fresh mint!</span></strong></p>",
